Three of seven organizational culture aspects are: Innovation and risk-taking: How much workers are encouraged to be innovative and take chances at work. Google is recognized for its inventive culture and willingness to try new things. Attention to detail: Employees are required to pay attention to details and work accurately. Mercedes-Benz, recognized for its accuracy and quality automotive manufacture, demonstrates this dimension. Outcome orientation: The organization's emphasis on objectives and outcomes rather than procedures. Amazon, famed for its customer pleasure and demonstrable results, demonstrates this characteristic. 